    "minides": "India's most affordable Countryman — locally assembled in Chennai, 156 hp 3-cylinder turbo, circular OLED touchscreen, ventilated + massage front seats, 505L boot, 5-star Euro NCAP. Under ₹48 lakh.",
    "description": "Launched on 17 June 2026 at ₹47.50 lakh (ex-showroom), the MINI Countryman C is the most accessible entry point into the Countryman family in India. Locally assembled at the BMW Group Plant in Chennai via CKD, it is positioned below the Countryman JCW All4 (₹64.90L) and the Countryman Electric. Available exclusively in the fully-loaded 'Favoured Pack', it is powered by a 1.5L 3-cylinder MINI TwinPower Turbo petrol engine (156 hp / 240 Nm) mated to a 7-speed Double-Clutch Steptronic Sport transmission. Key highlights: a 9.4-inch circular OLED MINI Central touchscreen, a panoramic glass roof with an interior lighting strip, 19-inch crystal-cut alloy wheels, champagne-gold grille surround and accents, Union Jack LED tail lamps, adaptive LED headlamps, ventilated and massaging front seats, a sliding/reclining rear bench, 505-litre boot (expandable to 1,450L), wireless Apple CarPlay/Android Auto, and a 5-star Euro NCAP rating. Rivals: BMW X1 (₹50.90L), Volvo XC40 (₹48.90L), Mercedes-Benz GLA (₹51.50L)."
  },
